===Etymology===
Refers to the Greek myth of Eris and the [[golden apple]], which attracted the [[desires]] of [[Hera]], [[Athena]], and [[Aphrodite]].

===Noun===
'''apple of one's eye''' (''Plural:'' '''apples of one's eye''')

# A favourite, a particular preference, or a loved one.
#: ''Sara was never the same after losing her daughter, the '''apple of Sara's eyes'''.''

